    "26167187": {
      "title": "Adjuvant therapy with agonistic antibodies to CD134 (OX40) increases local control after surgical or radiation therapy of cancer in mice",
      "abstract": "The tumor recurrence from residual local or micrometastatic disease remains a problem in cancer therapy. In patients with soft tissue sarcoma and the patients with inoperable nonsmall cell lung cancer, local recurrence is common and significant mortality is caused by the subsequent emergence of meta"
    },
    "14353267": {
      "title": "OX40 is a potent immune-stimulating target in late-stage cancer patients",
      "abstract": "This study offers clinical validation of a cancer therapy composed of a monoclonal antibody that can agonize signaling by the OX40 coreceptor on T cells, acting to enhance their antitumor properties as a generalized immunotherapy."
